<html lang="en" data-bs-theme="dark">

<head>
    <%- include('../../partials/head', {pageTitle: "Privacy Policy"}) %>

    <style>
        b {
            font-weight: 600;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<%- include('../../partials/headernav', {pageTitle: "Privacy Policy", loggedin: userLogged, username: username}) %>

<body>
    <main>
        <div class="container my-5 text-center">

            <img id="front-logo" src="/img/logo_new.png" alt="">
            <h1 class="mb-5  ">Privacy Policy</h1>

            <p class="lead">Your privacy is important to us. This policy outlines how we handle your personal
                information.</p>

        </div>

        <section>
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col">
                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h2>Effective Date: <span class="lead">July 27, 2025</span></h2>
                            <p><i>[Guerrillas of Liberation]</i> ("we", "our", "us") respects
                                your privacy and is committed
                                to
                                protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and
                                safeguard your information when you interact with our website and log in via Discord.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h3>1. Data Controller</h3>
                            <p>The Data Controller responsible for your personal data is:</p>
                            <p>
                                <b>Guerrillas of Liberation</b><br>
                                <b>Website:</b> <a href="/">gol-clan.com</a><br>
                                <b>Contact:</b> <a href="/contact">Contact Page</a>
                                <br>
                            </p>
                                <p>
                                    The <b>Data Protection Officer</b> can be contacted at:<br>
                                    <b>Contact Page:</b> <a href="/contact">Contact Page</a><br>
                                    <b>Email:</b> <a href="mailto:bluwolf01@hotmail.com">bluwolf01@hotmail.com</a>
                                </p>
                            <p>Guerrillas of Liberation determines the purposes and methods by which your data is
                                processed for community interactions, website functionality, and member communications.
                                If you have questions about your data or need to make a request under applicable data
                                protection laws, please get in touch via the contact page above.</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h3>2. Information We Collect</h3>
                            <p>When you log in using Discord authentication, we may receive the following data from
                                Discord:
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Discord User ID</li>
                                <li>Username and Avatar</li>
                                <li>Email address (if permission is granted)</li>
                                <li>Server membership details relevant to access permissions</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p><b>However</b>, the information/data that we collect is limited to:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Discord User ID</li>
                                <li>Server membership details relevant to access permissions</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>We <b>do not</b> collect Discord passwords, private messages, or any activity unrelated
                                to
                                login
                                authentication that is not listed above.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h3>3. Purpose of Processing</h3>
                            <p>We process your personal data for the following purposes:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>To authenticate and manage user access to our community</li>
                                <li>To assign appropriate roles and permissions</li>
                                <li>To deliver essential notifications (if you opt-in to email)</li>
                                <li>To maintain and improve user experience on the platform</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h3>4. Legal Basis for Processing</h3>
                            <p>We will process your personal data based on the following legal grounds:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Legitimate Interest: to ensure secure access and membership management</li>
                                <li>Consent: where optional data (such as email) is voluntarily provided</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h3>5. Data Sharing and Third Parties</h3>
                            <p>We do not sell or share your personal data with advertisers or third-party marketers.
                                However, certain data may be processed through:
                            </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Web hosting or infrastructure services used to operate the site</li>
                                <li>Discord, as a third-party authentication provider (View Discord's Privacy Policy)
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h3>6. Data Retention</h3>
                            <p>Personal data is retained only for as long as is necessary to fulfill the intended
                                purpose. We routinely review our storage practices and delete data if no longer required
                                or upon request.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h3>7. International Data Transfers</h3>
                            <p>Data may be stored or processed outside the UK. Where this occurs, appropriate safeguards
                                are implemented to ensure compliance with UK data protection standards.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h3>8. Your Rights</h3>
                            <p>In accordance with UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Access and view the data we hold about you</li>
                                <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
                                <li>Request deletion of your data (“right to be forgotten”)</li>
                                <li>Object to or restrict processing of your data</li>
                                <li>Withdraw your consent where processing relies on it</li>
                                <li>Lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h3>9. Security</h3>
                            <p>We take the security of your personal data seriously and implement appropriate technical
                                and organizational measures to protect it from unauthorized access, disclosure,
                                alteration, and destruction. Such as:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Encrypted data transmission via HTTPS</li>
                                <li>Access control limited to authorized administrators</li>
                                <li>Encryption of data in transit and at rest</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h3>10. Automated Decision-Making</h3>
                            <p>Where automated tools (e.g. bots or scripts) are used to assign community roles or access
                                levels based on Discord metadata, such logic is transparent and designed to ensure fair
                                and consistent community management.</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h3>11. Contact Us</h3>
                            <p>This policy may be updated periodically. We encourage users to check back regularly.
                                Material changes will be communicated through the website or Discord announcements. If
                                you have any questions or concerns about this policy, please contact us at <a
                                    href="mailto:bluwolf01@hotmail.com">bluwolf01@hotmail.com</a>.</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="border-bottom py-2">
                            <h3>12. Cookies</h3>
                            <p>Our website may use cookies or similar technologies to enhance user experience and ensure
                                proper functionality. Cookies are small data files stored on your device when you visit
                                the
                                site.</p>
                            <p>Types of Cookies We Use:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Essential Cookies: Necessary for core site operations, including login and session
                                    management.</li>
                                <li>Performance Cookies: Used to collect anonymized data on site usage for analytics and
                                    performance improvement.</li>
                                <li>Functionality Cookies: Enable user preferences, such as language settings or
                                    interface
                                    behavior.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>We do not use cookies for advertising or tracking across other sites.</p>
                            <p><strong>Managing Cookies:</strong></p>
                            <p>You can control or disable cookies through your browser settings. However, restricting
                                essential cookies may impact website functionality.</p>
                            <p>For more information on cookies and how to manage them, please visit
                                <a href="https://www.aboutcookies.org">https://www.aboutcookies.org</a></p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <script defer>
            var isloggedIn = "<%= loggedin %>"
        </script>
        <script src="/scripts/checkLogged.js"></script>
    </main>

